text: Panmure was a railway station in the town of Panmure, on the Warrnambool railway line in Victoria, Australia. The station was one of 35 closed to passenger traffic on 4 October 1981 as part of the New Deal timetable for country passengers. ==References== Category:Railway stations closed in 1981 Category:Disused railway stations in Victoria (Australia)
title: Panmure railway station, Victoria
